# Semicolons (JavaScript / TypeScript)

End every statement with **`;`** (no ASI). Includes `import`/`export`, declarations, `return`/`throw`/`break`/`continue`, calls, assignments.

**Same-line block comment:** `x = 1; /** note */` — semicolon **before** the comment.

**Commas / line breaks:** **Prettier** + `.prettierrc`; this rule is only semicolons.

```typescript
const title = "Soup";
import { useState } from "react";
const ref = useRef(false); /** avoids double fire */
```

**New and edited** code; follow **ESLint + Prettier** if they disagree.
